    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>In Mozilla Chairperson Mitchell Baker's DrupalCon Denver 2012 keynote she announced a new web authentication system they are developing called <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/persona/" rel="nofollow">Mozilla Persona</a>. It's a federated and open standard that respects privacy. I wanted to use this technology for my own projects so I created the <a href="https://drupal.org/project/persona" rel="nofollow">Drupal module</a>.</p>
<p>I also created a <a href="https://see.drupalpersona.me/" rel="nofollow">demo site</a> (hosting kindly provided by <a href="https://www.getpantheon.com/" rel="nofollow">Pantheon</a>).</p>
<p>Persona and Drupal are a great match - I've submitted a <a href="https://prague2013.drupal.org/session/mozilla-persona-webs-decentralised-identity-api" rel="nofollow">session</a> to <a href="https://prague2013.drupal.org/" rel="nofollow">DrupalCon Prague</a>.</p>
